INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 15, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>Congratulations!  You now have a fully functional installation of CMS and you are <em>almost</em> ready to start building your site.  First thing though, you should click <a href=\"install/upgrade.php\">here</a> to check if your site requires a database upgrade.  After you have confirmed you are up to date, then we can get cracking on the site development!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Below is some short introduction text to the basics of CMS Made Simple.  The rest of this site is devoted to showing some of the layouts that can be achieved using various menu modules and other tricks.  Just look at the source to see how they were achieved.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You have to login as the administrator (with the username/password you mentioned at first step of installation process) on your site at http://yourwebsite.com/cms/admin.</p>\r\n<p>If you are right now on your own default install, you can probably just click <a href=\"admin/\">this link</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Menus</h5>\r\n<p>As you create your content, each piece will have the option of a parent to assign to the selected Content piece.  This hierarchy is what drives the menu you see on the left side of this page.  When you login to the admin site, you will see the content hierarchy when you navigate to Content-->Pages.  To change the order of items in the menu, use the move arrows to the right of each content piece.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h5>Learning CMS Made Simple</h5>\r\n<p>On these example pages many of the features of the default installation of CMS Made Simple are described and demonstrated. You can learn about how to use different kinds of menus, templates and stylesheets and extensions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Read about how to use CMS Made Simple in the <a href=\"http://www.cmsmadesimple.org/Documentation.shtml\">documentation</a>. In case you need any help the community is always at your service, in the <a href=\"http://forum.cmsmadesimple.org\">forum</a> or the <a href=\"http://www.cmsmadesimple.org/IRC.shtml\">IRC</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h5>License</h5>\r\n<p>CMS is released under the <a href=\"http://www.gnu.org/licenses/licenses.html#GPL\">GPL</a> license</p>', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 29, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>There are currently 4 main content types in version {cms_version} \"{cms_versionname}\":</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Content</li>\r\n<li>Link</li>\r\n<li>Separator</li>\r\n<li>Section Header</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The <strong>content</strong> type is simply a regular page.  That is what this page you are reading is.  Here you can put any content that you would put on a regular page.  The layout of these types of pages are controlled by the templates.  For each <strong>content</strong> page you create you must choose a template for it.  If you login as admin and change the template of this page, you will see exactly how it works.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <strong>separator</strong> type is just what it sounds like, a separator that appears on the menus.  This type follows the hierarchy set in in content management pages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <strong>link</strong> type is just what it sounds like, a link to another page, either internal or external.  This <strong>Link</strong> type also shows up in the menu following the same hierarchy rules as the <strong>content</strong> type.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <strong>section header</strong> type is used to break up menus into groupings.  This is unrelated to the hierarchy, as the section headers have no associated pages with them.  They are just a little bit of text to say what the next few links are in reference to.</p>\r\n', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 28, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>One of the little known features of CMS Made Simple is the User Defined tag.  Basically, this allows you to write PHP code inside the Admin Panel.  Use the \'Add User Defined Tag\' button in Extensions/User-defined tags in the Admin Panel, write some code, and then insert into a template or page with {literal}{newpluginname}{/literal}.  Simple!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As an example, I\'ve put together a one line plugin that will show your current User Agent information (which browser you\'re using).  The output is right here: <b>{user_agent}</b>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you\'re not looking at the source, all that is in the page is a {literal}{user_agent}{/literal}.  To see how this code works, edit the user_agent tag in the Extensions/User-defined tags page of the admin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a VERY powerful feature if used right.  Remember, user defined tags do not get cached, therefore, scripts to rotate ad banners and such will work just fine. Note also that tags code have to be written <em>without</em> opening < ? php  and ending  ? > tags.</p>', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 19, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>Here we display a number of different ways to use the menus and templates that come with the CMS Made Simple package.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are three different kinds of navigation systems that come with CMS Made Simple:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>Bulletmenu </em>-- This is the simplest navigation. It is basically just an unordered list that can be styled with CSS to get it to look the way you want. Through CSS you can make the bulletmenu either vertical or horizontal.</li>\r\n<li><em>EllNav </em>-- The EllNav module splits up the menu with the top level in one place and the page-specific menu in another. That is, the top level is displayed on every page, while the sub-levels are specific for each page. It\'s called EllNav beacuse one way of using this is the traditional L-shaped navigation.</li>\r\n<li><em>CSS Menu </em>-- This is a drop-down menu that is using only CSS (although some Javascript is required for Internet Explorer). It can be either vertical or horizontal.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 19, 'string', 'block1', null, null, null, null, '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 20, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<h2>{title}</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This page is to display the use of the News module and inserting Smarty tags to display modules in general. A module is an extension that adds functionality to your default CMS Made Simple install. More modules can be downloaded from the <a href=\"http://dev.cmsmadesimple.org\">CMSMS Forge</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To display a list of news items you insert the tag &#123;cms_module module=\'news\' number=\'5\' category=\'General\'}. In this case that tag is inserted in the template. But it can also be inserted on a page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are a number of parameters that can be used in conjunction with this tag. To read about how a module is used, navigate to Extensions/Modules in the Admin Panel and click on \"Help\" for the module you want to read about.</p>\r\n\r\n', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 27, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>These are the other tags that come with the default installation of CMS Made Simple. They are only inserted in this particular page. For each of the tags there is an example of how it looks like when it is used.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}adsense}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br /><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br /><br /><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code style=\"margin: 0; padding: 0;\">{ldelim}adsense ad_client=\"pub-random#\" ad_width=\"125\"<br /> ad_height=\"125\" ad_format=\"125x125_as\"}</code>\r\n<br />This tag will take the basic parameters that would be provided by the <a href=\"https://www.google.com/adsense/\" taget=\"_blank\">Google adsense program</a> and puts them in a easy to use tag that makes your templates look much cleaner.<br />\r\n      {adsense ad_client=\"pub-7958561174011032\" ad_width=\"125\" ad_height=\"125\" ad_format=\"125x125_as\"}\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}contact_form}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}contact_form email=\"yourname@yourdomain.com\"}</code><br />\r\nDisplay\'s a simple contact form. <br />\r\n{contact_form email=\"yourname@yourdomain.com\"}\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}current_date}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}current_date format=\"%A %d-%b-%y %T %Z\"}</code><br />\r\nPrints the current date and time.<br >\r\n{current_date format=\"%A %d-%b-%y %T %Z\"}\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}edit}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}edit}</code><br />\r\nCreates a link to edit the page in the Admin Panel.<br />\r\n{edit}\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}embed}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}embed url=\"http://www.cmsmadesimple.org\"}</code><br />\r\nEnable inclusion (embeding) of any other application into the CMS. The most usual use could be a forum. \r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}googlepr}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}googlepr}</code><br />\r\nDisplay\'s a number that represents your google pagerank.<br />\r\n{googlepr}\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}html_blob}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}html_blob name=\'footer\'}</code><br />\r\nInserts an html blob into your template or page. The code for the footer of this page is in a html blob. \r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}menu_text}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}menu_text}</code><br />\r\nPrints the menu text of the page.<br />\r\n{menu_text}<br />\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}modified_date}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br >\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}modified_date format=\"%A %d-%b-%y %T %Z\"}</code><br />\r\nPrints the date and time the page was last modified. <br />\r\n{modified_date format=\"%A %d-%b-%y %T %Z\"}\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}print}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}print}</code><br />\r\nCreates a link to only the content of the page.<br />\r\n{print}\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}search}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}search}</code><br />\r\nSearches your website using Google\'s search engine.<br />\r\n{search}\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}startExpandCollapse} {ldelim}stopExpandCollapse}\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br /><br /><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}startExpandCollapse id=\"name\" title=\"Click Here\"}</code><br />Text here<br />\r\n<code>{ldelim}stopExpandCollapse id=\"name\" title=\"Click Here\"}</code><br />\r\nEnables content to be expandable and collapsable.<br />\r\n{startExpandCollapse id=\"name\" title=\"Click Here\"}Here is some text that displays when expanded. Click the \"Click here\" link to collapse it again.\r\n {stopExpandCollapse} \r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<hr class=\"tags\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}sitemap}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}sitemap}</code><br />\r\nPrints out a sitemap.<br />\r\n{sitemap}\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 14, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>This is a page with only one level of navigation, placed at the top.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <em>bulletmenu</em> tag could easily be used. But here we have used the <em>EllNav</em> module to only show the top level. The code inserted in the template is <code>{ldelim}cms_module module=\'EllNav\' horizontal=1 toponly=1 cssid=\'topmenu\'}</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you want more levels (but still top level at the top of the page) you could either use {cms_selflink page=\'CSS_Menu\' text=\'drop-down CSS menus\'} or split menus with the {cms_selflink page=\'L_navigation_Split_Menu\' text=\'EllNav\'} module, to put the sub-levels on another part of the page.</p>', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 26, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>These tags are inserted in the template that this page is using. They are therefore displayed on all pages using this template.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}breadcrumbs}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br /><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}breadcrumbs delimiter=\'»\' initial=\'1\'}</code><br />\r\nBreadcrumbs are a navigational technique displaying all visited pages leading from the home page to the currently viewed page.<br />\r\nYou find it under the header on this page.\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}cms_version}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}cms_version}</code><br />\r\nDisplays current version number of CMS Made Simple. <br />\r\nSee the footer on this page.\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}cms_versionname}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}cms_versionname}</code><br />\r\nDisplays current version name of CMS Made Simple. <br />\r\nSee the footer on this page.\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}cms_selflink}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br /><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}cms_selflink dir=\"previous\"} {ldelim}cms_selflink dir=\"next\"}</code><br />\r\nCreates a link to another CMSMS content page inside your template or content.<br />\r\n See bottom of the content area on this page.\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}content}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br /><br /><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}content}</code><br />\r\nThis is where the content for your page will be displayed. It\'s inserted into the template and changed based on the current page being displayed.<br />\r\nThe area of this page starting with the header \"Tags used in the template that this page is using\" is inserted where the {ldelim}content} tag is placed in the template.\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}stylesheet}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br /><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}stylesheet}</code><br />\r\nGets stylesheet information from the system. By default, it grabs all of the stylesheets attached to the current template.<br />\r\nThis tag is inserted between the &lt;head> tags in the template that this page is using and grabs all stylesheets attached to the template.\r\n</div>\r\n<hr class=\"tags\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"tagtitle\">\r\n   {ldelim}title}\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"left\">\r\n   <em>Syntax used</em><br />\r\n   <em>Display</em><br />\r\n   <em>Example</em>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"right\">\r\n<code>{ldelim}title}</code><br />\r\nPrints the title of the page.<br />\r\nThe header of this page is the title of the page and is printed where the {ldelim}title} tag is placed in the template (or page).\r\n</div>', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 13, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>For pages with navigation only to the left the <em>bulletmenu</em> tag is the easiest option. Just put <code>{ldelim}bulletmenu}</code>  (or <code>{ldelim}bulletmenu collapse=\'1\'}</code> if you want sub-levels collapsed by default) in your template where you want the menu to appear.</p>', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 22, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>With this approach you can split the navigation in two parts. On this page the top level in the page hierarchy is displayed horizontally and depending on what page is displayed a localized sub-menu is displayed vertically to the left. In this case the sub-menu to the left displays the sub-levels to \"Menus/Navigation systems\".</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On this page we have inserted <code>{ldelim}cms_module module=\'EllNav\' horizontal=1 toponly=1}</code> in the template where we want the top level to be displayed and <br /><code>{ldelim}cms_module module=\'EllNav\' showtoplevel=0}</code> <br />where we want the sub-levels to display.</p>', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 17, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>This is a drop-down menu that is using only CSS (although some Javascript is required for Internet Explorer). It can be either vertical or horizontal. Select the horizontal version by navigating to Menus/Navigation systems --> Drop-down (CSSMenu) --> Horizontal in the navigation to the left.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The code we have inserted in the template that this page is using is simply <code>{ldelim}cms_module module=\'cssmenu\'}</code>. You style the menu in the stylesheet <em>Default CSSMenu Vert</em> or <em>Default CSSMenu Horiz</em> for the horizontal CSSMenu.<p>\r\n\r\n<p>But to be on the safe side, copy this stylesheet and attach the new stylesheet to the template instead (and make your changes in the new stylesheet). Then you can always revert to the default stylesheet if something goes wrong.</p>\r\n\r\n', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}content_props ( CONTENT_ID, TYPE, PROP_NAME, PARAM1, PARAM2, PARAM3, CONTENT, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 21, 'string', 'content_en', null, null, null, '<p>For each page in CMS Made Simple you choose what template to use. A template is the html code with placeholders for content, navigation and extensions. To each template you can also attach one or more stylesheets to style the different elements of your page, as well as customize the layout.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These example pages basically use the same html template (the only difference is\r\nwhat navigation system that is used and if it\'s using one or two content blocks). Without touching the html templates you can then get widely different layouts by using only CSS (Cascading Stylesheets).</p> \r\n\r\n<p>We have grouped related styles in separate stylesheets to make them easier to edit. Each of the default templates therefore has seven or eight stylesheets attached. But only one of those is template-specific.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These are the stylesheets that are used for the default CMSMS templates:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Stylesheets that are attached to all default templates</strong>\r\n  <ul>\r\n\r\n    <li><em>Layout </em>--\r\nHere you set general layout settings, that are the same for all the\r\ndefault CMSMS templates. But for each project you work on this\r\nstylesheet needs to be customized.</li>\r\n    <li><em>Typography </em>-- This is where you do all the styling for fonts, links, headings, images, lists etc.</li>\r\n    <li><em>Colours</em>-- All the colors are gathered in this stylesheet. The only properties here are color, background and border-color. Don\'t add any other properties here or it may affect the layout of your entire site! However, for now the colors of menus are in the menu stylesheets.</li>\r\n    <li><em>Forms </em>--\r\nTo more easily make forms to look the same across different browsers,\r\nthe styling for forms is in its own stylesheet. You will not need to\r\ntouch this very often.</li>\r\n  <li><em>Tools </em>--\r\nThis is a stylesheet that needs to be attached to all templates for\r\ncross-browser behaviour. But you don\'t really need to touch it at all.</li>\r\n\r\n  </ul>\r\n</li>  \r\n\r\n<li><strong>Navigation stylesheets</strong>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li><em>Nav-Horizontal / Nav-Vertical </em>--\r\nDepending on the layout of your template you need to attach one or both\r\nof these stylesheets. You only need to change a few things in these\r\nstylesheets, to style the menu to look the way you want.</li>\r\n    <li><em>Default CSSMenu Horiz / Default CSSMenu Vert </em>-- If you rather use a drop-down CSS Menu, then either of these two stylesheets is used.</li>\r\n\r\n  </ul>\r\n</li>\r\n  \r\n<li><strong>Template-specific stylesheets</strong>\r\n  <ul>\r\n  <li><em>Layout-XXX </em>--\r\nThere is one stylesheet that is specific for each template. This is\r\nwhere you do the layout (and perhaps styling) that only applies to that\r\nparticular template. For example, by changing only this stylesheet you\r\ncan have the menu to appear to the top or the side, left or right.</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 20, 'Typography', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style */\r\n\r\n/* TYPOGRAPHY */\r\n	body {\r\n		text-align: left;\r\n		font-family: Verdana, Geneva, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\r\n		font-size: 76%;\r\n                line-height: 1em;\r\n	}\r\n	div {\r\n		font-size: 1em;\r\n	}\r\n	img {\r\n		border: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	\r\n/* LINKS */\r\n	a,\r\n	a:link \r\n	a:active, a:visited {\r\n		text-decoration: underline;\r\n	}\r\n\r\n	a:hover {\r\n	text-decoration: none;\r\n	}\r\n/* END LINKS */\r\n	\r\n/* HEADINGS */\r\n	h1 {\r\n		font-size: 2em;\r\n		line-height: 1.5em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	h2 {\r\n		font-size: 1.5em;\r\n                line-height: 1.5em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	h3 {\r\n		font-size: 1.3em;\r\n		line-height: 1.3em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;\r\n		padding:0;\r\n	}\r\n	#menu_vert h2 {\r\n		margin-left: 10px;\r\n	}\r\n	h4 {\r\n		font-size: 1.2em;\r\n		line-height: 1.3em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 0.25em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	h5 {\r\n		font-size: 1.1em;\r\n		line-height: 1.3em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 0.25em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	h6 {\r\n		font-size: 1em;\r\n		line-height: 1.3em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 0.25em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n/* END HEADINGS */\r\n\r\n/* TEXT */\r\n	p {\r\n		font-size: 1em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 1.5em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n		line-height:1.4em;\r\n	}\r\n	blockquote {\r\n		border-left: 10px solid #ddd;\r\n		margin-left: 10px;\r\n	}\r\n	pre {\r\n		font-family: monospace;\r\n		font-size: 1.0em;\r\n	}\r\n	strong, b {\r\n		font-weight: bold;\r\n	}\r\n	em, i {\r\n		font-style:italic;\r\n	}\r\n    code {\r\n        font-family: \"Courier New\", Courier, monospace;\r\n        font-size: 1em;\r\n        white-space: pre;\r\n    }\r\n/* END TEXT */\r\n	\r\n/* LISTS */\r\n	#main ul {\r\n        line-height:1.4em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 1.5em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	#main ul li {\r\n		margin: 0 0 0.25em 30px;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	ol {\r\n		font-size: 1.0em;\r\n		line-height: 1.4em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 1.5em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	ol li {\r\n		font-size: 1.0em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 0.25em 30px;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	dl {\r\n		margin: 0 0 1.5em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n		line-height: 1.4em;\r\n	}\r\n	dl dt {\r\n		font-weight: bold;\r\n		margin: 0.25em 0 0.25em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	dl dd {\r\n		margin: 0 0 0 30px;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n/* END LISTS */\r\n	\r\n	\r\n/* TABLE */\r\n	table {\r\n        font-size: 1em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 1.5em 0;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	table caption {\r\n		font-weight: bold;\r\n		margin: 0 0 0 0;\r\n		padding: 0 0 1.5em 0;\r\n	}\r\n	th {\r\n		font-weight: bold;\r\n		text-align: left;\r\n	}\r\n	td {\r\n		font-size: 1em;\r\n	}\r\n/* END TABLE */	\r\n	\r\n	hr {\r\n		   \r\n	}\r\n	div.hr {\r\n		height: 1px;\r\n		margin: 1.5em 10px;\r\n		border-bottom: 1px dotted black;\r\n	}\r\n	\r\n/* END TYPOGRAPHY */	', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 29, 'Colours', '/* Layout sections */\r\n	body {\r\n		background: #ccc;\r\n		color: #333;\r\n		}\r\n		\r\n	div#page {\r\n		border: 1px solid #000;\r\n		background: #fff;\r\n	    }\r\n		\r\n	div#header {\r\n		color: #fff;\r\n		}\r\n		\r\n	div#footer {\r\n		color: #fff;\r\n		background-color: #385C72;\r\n		}\r\n		\r\n/* Links */		\r\n	a,\r\n	a:link \r\n	a:active, a:visited {\r\n		color: #385C72;\r\n	}\r\n\r\n/* Headings */	\r\n	h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {\r\n		color: #000;\r\n	}', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 11, 'Layout Bulletmenu Vert 2C', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n/* NAV BAR ON THE LEFT AND TWO COLUMNS OF CONTENT */\r\n    div#content {\r\n        position: relative;\r\n        width: 760px;\r\n        \r\n        margin: 15px 20px 20px 0;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n        \r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n    div#main {\r\n        float: right;\r\n        width: 340px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n        \r\n        margin-right: 210px;\r\n        margin-left: -220px;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_vert {\r\n        float: left;\r\n        width: 200px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#content2 {\r\n        float: right;\r\n        width: 200px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n        \r\n        margin-right: -340px;\r\n        margin-left: 200px;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz {\r\n        display: none;\r\n    }\r\n/* END CONTENT */', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 12, 'Layout EllNav H Only 1C', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n/* NAV BAR AT THE TOP AND ONE COLUMN OF CONTENT */\r\n    div#content {\r\n        position: relative;\r\n        width: 741px;\r\n        margin: 15px auto 20px auto;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n    div#main {\r\n        width: 100%;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_vert {\r\n        display: none;\r\n    }\r\n    div#content2 {\r\n        width: 100%;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz {\r\n      margin: 0;\r\n      display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n/* END CONTENT */', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 28, 'Temp (for example pages)', 'div.tagtitle{\r\n   margin-bottom: 5px;\r\n   font-weight: bold;\r\n}\r\n\r\ndiv.left {\r\n   float: left;\r\n   width: 80px;\r\n   line-height: 140%;\r\n}\r\n\r\ndiv.right {\r\n   margin-left: 100px;\r\n   line-height: 140%;\r\n   padding-bottom: 5px;\r\n}\r\n\r\nhr.tags {\r\n   clear: both;\r\n   height: 1px !important;\r\n   border: none !important;\r\n   background-color: #006699 !important;\r\n   margin-bottom: 15px !important;\r\n}', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 14, 'Layout EllNav H/V L 2Col', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n/* NAV BAR AT THE TOP, LOCAL NAV ON THE LEFT AND TWO COLUMNS OF CONTENT */\r\n\r\n    div#content {\r\n        position: relative;\r\n        width: 761px;\r\n        \r\n        margin: 15px auto 20px 0;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n        \r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n   div#main {\r\n        float: left;\r\n        padding: 0 20px;\r\n        width: 340px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#content2 {\r\n        float: right;\r\n        width: 190px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_vert {\r\n        float: left;\r\n        width: 190px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz {\r\n\r\n        width: 100%;\r\n        \r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n/* END CONTENT */', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 15, 'Layout EllNav H/V L 1Col', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n/* NAV BAR AT THE TOP, LOCAL NAVIGATION ON THE LEFT AND ONE COLUMN OF CONTENT */\r\n    div#content {\r\n        position: relative;\r\n        width: 761px;\r\n        \r\n        margin: 15px auto 20px 0;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n\r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n    div#main {\r\n        float: right;\r\n        width: 550px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_vert {\r\n        float: left;\r\n        width: 190px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#content2 {\r\n        display: none;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz {\r\n          width: 100%;\r\n        \r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n/* END CONTENT */', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 16, 'Layout EllNav H/V R 1Col', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n/* NAV BAR AT THE TOP AND TWO COLUMNS OF CONTENT */\r\n    div#content {\r\n        position: relative;\r\n        width: 761px;\r\n        margin: 15px 0 20px auto;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n    div#main {\r\n        float: left;\r\n        width: 540px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_vert {\r\n        float: right;\r\n        width: 200px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#content2 {\r\n        display: none;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    div#menu_horiz {\r\n        width: 100%;\r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n/* END CONTENT */', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 17, 'Nav-Horizontal', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n/* NAV */\r\n\r\n    * html div#menu_horiz {\r\n        /* hide ie/mac \\*/\r\n        height: 1%;\r\n        /* end hide */\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz {\r\n      background-color: #ECECEC;\r\n      width: 100%;\r\n      margin: 0;\r\n      text-align: center;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz ul {\r\n        margin: 0;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n        list-style: none;\r\n        border-bottom: 1px solid #C0C0C0;\r\n        border-left:  1px solid #C0C0C0;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz li {\r\n        float: left;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n        list-style: none;\r\n        margin: 0 ;\r\n        border-right: 1px solid #C0C0C0;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz li a {\r\n        border-right: none;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz a,\r\n    div#menu_horiz a:link,\r\n    div#menu_horiz a:active,\r\n    div#menu_horiz a:visited {\r\n        display: inline-block;\r\n        padding: 5px 10px 5px 10px; \r\n\r\n        /* hide from ie/mac \\*/\r\n        display: block;\r\n        /* end hide */\r\n\r\n        text-decoration: none;\r\n        margin: 0;\r\n        color: #18507C;\r\n        background: #ECECEC;\r\n    }\r\n#menu_horiz li a:hover {\r\n	background-color: #abb0b6;\r\n}\r\n    div#menu_horiz .active {\r\n        display: inline-block;\r\n\r\n        /* hide from ie/mac \\*/\r\n        display: block;\r\n        /* end hide */\r\n        \r\n	background-color: #abb0b6;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    div#menu_horiz .current a,\r\n    div#menu_horiz .current a:link,\r\n    div#menu_horiz .current a:active,\r\n    div#menu_horiz .current a:visited,\r\n    div#menu_horiz .current a:hover,\r\n    div#menu_horiz .active a,\r\n    div#menu_horiz .active a:link,\r\n    div#menu_horiz .active a:active,\r\n    div#menu_horiz .active a:visited,\r\n    div#menu_horiz .active a:hover \r\n{\r\n	background-color: #abb0b6;\r\n    }\r\n/* END NAV */', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 18, 'Nav-Vertical', '#menu_vert, #menu_vert ul {\r\n  margin: 0;\r\n  padding: 0;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n#menu_vert ul {\r\n  width: 100%; /* Width of Menu Items */\r\n  border-top: 1px solid #006699;\r\n  border-right: 1px solid #006699;\r\n  background: #ececec;\r\n  }\r\n#menu_vert li {\r\n  position: relative;\r\n  list-style: none;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n#menu_vert li a {\r\n  display: block;\r\n  text-decoration: none;\r\n  padding: 5px 5px 5px 10px;\r\n  border-bottom: 1px solid #006699;\r\n  color: #18507C;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n/* Fix IE. Hide from IE Mac \\*/\r\n* html #menu_vert li { float: left; height: 1%; }\r\n* html #menu_vert li a { height: 1%; }\r\n/* End */\r\n\r\n    div#menu_vert ul ul li a, \r\n    div#menu_vert ul ul li a:link, \r\n    div#menu_vert ul ul li a:visited  {\r\n        display: block;\r\n        padding: 3px 5px 3px 25px;\r\n        border-bottom: none;\r\n        font-size: 90%;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_vert ul ul  {\r\n      border-right: none;\r\n      border-top: none;\r\n      border-bottom: 1px solid #006699;\r\n      padding-bottom: 5px;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    div#menu_vert ul ul ul i a, \r\n    div#menu_vert ul ul ul li a:link, \r\n    div#menu_vert ul ul ul li a:visited  {\r\n        padding-left: 40px;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_vert ul ul ul  {\r\n      border-bottom: none;\r\n    }\r\n#menu_vert li ul li a { padding: 5px 5px; } /* Sub Menu Styles */\r\n\r\n/* fixed image flicker by adding .cssmenu-vertical ul */\r\n\r\n#menu_vert li a:hover {\r\n	background-color: #abb0b6;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.currentpage, .current\r\n{\r\n	list-style-type: square;\r\n	display: inline;\r\n	background-color: #abb0b6;\r\n}\r\n', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 19, 'Tools', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n/* clearing */\r\n	.stretch,\r\n	.clear {\r\n		clear:both; \r\n		height:1px; \r\n		margin:0; \r\n		padding:0; \r\n		font-size: 15px;\r\n		line-height: 1px;\r\n	}\r\n	.clearfix:after {\r\n		content: \".\"; \r\n		display: block; \r\n		height: 0; \r\n		clear: both; \r\n		visibility: hidden;\r\n	}\r\n	.menu_horiz:after {\r\n		content: \".\"; \r\n		display: block; \r\n		height: 0; \r\n		clear: both; \r\n		visibility: hidden;\r\n	}\r\n	* html>body .clearfix {\r\n		display: inline-block; \r\n		width: 100%;\r\n	}\r\n	* html>body .menu_horiz{\r\n		display: inline-block; \r\n		width: 100%;\r\n	}\r\n	\r\n	* html .clearfix {\r\n		/* Hides from IE-mac \\*/\r\n		height: 1%;\r\n		/* End hide from IE-mac */\r\n	}\r\n	* html .menu_horiz{\r\n		/* Hides from IE-mac \\*/\r\n		height: 1%;\r\n		/* End hide from IE-mac */\r\n	}\r\n/* end clearing */\r\n\r\n\r\n/* replace */\r\n	.replace {\r\n		display:block;\r\n		\r\n		background-repeat: no-repeat;\r\n		background-position: left top;\r\n		background-color:transparent;\r\n	}\r\n	/* tidy these up */\r\n	.replace * {\r\n		text-indent: -10000px;\r\n		display:block;\r\n		\r\n		background-repeat: no-repeat;\r\n		background-position: left top;\r\n		background-color:transparent;\r\n	}\r\n	.replace a {\r\n		text-indent:0;\r\n	}\r\n	.replace a span {\r\n		text-indent:-10000px;\r\n	}\r\n/* end replace */\r\n\r\n\r\n/* accessibility */\r\n     span.accesskey {\r\n     	text-decoration:none;\r\n     }\r\n     .accessibility {\r\n     	position: absolute;\r\n     	top: -999em;\r\n     	left: -999em;\r\n     }\r\n/* end accessibility */', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 8, 'Forms', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n/* FORM ELEMENTS */\r\n	form {\r\n		margin:0;\r\n		padding:0;\r\n	}\r\n	form div,\r\n	form p {\r\n		font-size: 1em;\r\n		margin: 0 0 1em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	label {\r\n		font-weight: bold;\r\n	}\r\n	fieldset {\r\n		border: 1px solid #eee;\r\n		padding: 5px 10px;\r\n		margin: 0 0 1.5em 0;\r\n	}\r\n	fieldset legend {\r\n		color: #666;\r\n		font-size: 1.1em;\r\n		font-weight: bold;\r\n		margin: 0 0 0 0px;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n		background-color: white;\r\n	}\r\n	* html fieldset legend {\r\n		margin: 0 0 10px -10px;\r\n	}\r\n	fieldset ul {\r\n		list-style: none;\r\n		margin: 0 0 1.5em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	fieldset ul li {\r\n		list-style: none;\r\n		margin: 0 0 0.5em 0;\r\n		padding: 0;\r\n	}\r\n     \r\n	\r\n	input, select, textarea {\r\n		font-size:1em; \r\n		font-family: arial, helvetica, verdana, sans-serif;\r\n        \r\n        margin: 0;\r\n		padding: 2px;\r\n	}\r\n	\r\n	input, select {\r\n		vertical-align:middle;\r\n	}\r\n	textarea {\r\n		width: 200px;\r\n		height: 8em;\r\n	}\r\n	\r\n	input.check {\r\n		border: none;\r\n		width: auto;\r\n		height: auto;\r\n		margin: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	input.radio {\r\n		border: none;\r\n		width: auto;\r\n		height: auto;\r\n		margin: 0;\r\n	}\r\n	input.file {\r\n		height: auto;\r\n		width: 250px;\r\n	}\r\n	input.readonly {\r\n		background-color: transparent;\r\n		border: none;\r\n	}\r\n	input.button {\r\n		width: 10em;\r\n		border:1px solid black;\r\n		background-color: #ddd;\r\n	}\r\n	input.image {\r\n		border: none;\r\n		width: auto;\r\n		height: auto; \r\n	}\r\n	\r\n    form div.submit {\r\n		margin: 1em 0;\r\n	}\r\n    form div.submit input {\r\n		height: 2em;\r\n        width: 15em;\r\n	}\r\n/* END FORM ELEMENTS */\r\n		', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 9, 'Layout', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n/* SITE SPECIFIC LAYOUT */\r\n    body {\r\n        margin: 0;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n        text-align: center;\r\n    }\r\n    div#page {\r\n        width: 780px;\r\n        margin:  10px auto 10px auto;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    /* HEADER */\r\n        div#header {\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 0;\r\n            height: 80px;\r\n            background: #385C72 url(images/cms/logo1.png) no-repeat 0 12px;            \r\n            text-align: center;\r\n        }\r\n\r\n    /* END HEADER */\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    /* CONTENT */\r\n        div#content {\r\n\r\n        }\r\n        \r\n        /* MAIN */\r\n            div#main {\r\n\r\n            }\r\n        /* END MAIN */\r\n        \r\n        /* SUB */\r\n            div#sub {\r\n                \r\n            }\r\n        /* END SUB */\r\n        \r\n    /* END CONTENT */\r\n    \r\n    \r\n    /* FOOTER */\r\n        div#footer {\r\n\r\n        }\r\n\r\n        div#footer p {\r\n            font-size: 0.8em;\r\n            margin: 0;\r\n            padding: 15px;\r\n            text-align: center;\r\n        }\r\n    /* END FOOTER */\r\n/* END LAYOUT */\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\ndiv.breadcrumbs {\r\n   padding-top: 10px;\r\n   padding-left: 10px;\r\n   text-align: left;\r\n   font-size: 90%;\r\n }', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 10, 'Layout Bulletmenu Vert 1C', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n/* NAV BAR ON THE LEFT AND ONE COLUMN OF CONTENT */\r\n    div#content {\r\n        position: relative;\r\n        width: 780px;\r\n        margin: 15px auto 20px 0;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n        \r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n    div#main {\r\n        float: right;\r\n        width: 540px;\r\n        padding: 0 15px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_vert {\r\n        float: left;\r\n        width: 200px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n        margin-left: 0;\r\n    }\r\n    div#content2 {\r\n        display: none;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz {\r\n        display: none;\r\n    }\r\n/* END CONTENT */', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 24, 'Layout CSSMenu Vert 1C', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n\r\n/* NAV BAR ON THE LEFT AND ONE COLUMN OF CONTENT */\r\n    div#content {\r\n        position: relative;\r\n        width: 780px;\r\n        margin: 15px auto 20px auto;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n    div#main {\r\n        float: right;\r\n        width: 550px;\r\n        margin-right: 10px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_vert {\r\n        float: left;\r\n        width: 200px;\r\n        display: inline;\r\n        margin-left: 0;\r\n    }\r\n    div#content2 {\r\n        display: none;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz {\r\n        display: none;\r\n    }\r\n/* END CONTENT */', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 23, 'Layout CSSMenu Horiz 1C', '/* A CSS Framework by Mike Stenhouse of Content with Style, adapted to CMSMS by Daniel Westergren */\r\n\r\n \r\n/* NAV BAR AT THE TOP AND ONE COLUMN OF CONTENT */\r\n    div#content {\r\n        width: 761px;\r\n        \r\n        margin: 10px auto 20px 10px;\r\n        padding: 0;\r\n        \r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n    div#main {\r\n        width: 100%;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_vert {\r\n        display: none;\r\n    }\r\n    div#content2 {\r\n        width: 100%;\r\n    }\r\n    div#menu_horiz {\r\n        width: 100%;\r\n        text-align: left;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n/* END CONTENT */', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 25, 'Default CSSMenu Horiz', '#primary-nav { \r\n	margin: 0px; \r\n	padding: 0px; \r\n	list-style: none; \r\n        border-bottom: 1px solid #C0C0C0;\r\n        overflow: hidden;\r\n        background-color: #ECECEC;\r\n        width: 100%;\r\n	}\r\n#primary-nav ul { \r\n	margin: 0px; \r\n	padding: 0px; \r\n	list-style: none; \r\n	border: 1px solid #d2d2d2; \r\n	left: -999em; \r\n	margin-left: -11px; \r\n	margin-top: 5px; \r\n	position: absolute; \r\n	width: 180px;\r\n }\r\n#primary-nav ul ul { \r\n	margin-top: -16px; \r\n	margin-left: 172px; \r\n	}\r\n\r\n#primary-nav a { \r\n	color: #18507C; \r\n	display: block; \r\n	font-size: 12px; \r\n	text-decoration: none; \r\n	}\r\n#primary-nav ul a { \r\n	width: 160px; \r\n\r\n	}\r\n\r\n#primary-nav li { \r\n	background-color: #ECECEC; \r\n	border-right: 1px solid #00ACE6; \r\n\r\n	background-position: top right; \r\n	background-repeat: no-repeat; \r\n	float: left; padding: 5px 10px 5px 10px; \r\n	}\r\n#primary-nav ul li { \r\n	background-color: #F7F9FB; \r\n	background-image: none; \r\n	border: none; clear: left; \r\n	padding: 3px 12px 3px 8px; \r\n	}\r\n#primary-nav li.active { \r\n	background-color: #E5EAF1; \r\n	background-image: url(../images/primary-navcb.gif); \r\n	background-position: top right; \r\n	background-repeat: no-repeat; \r\n	}	\r\n#primary-nav li.menuparent { \r\n	background-position: center right; \r\n	background-repeat: no-repeat; \r\n	}\r\n\r\n#primary-nav li li.menuparent { \r\n	background-image: url(modules/CSSMenu/images/arrow-right.gif); \r\n	background-position: center right; \r\n	background-repeat: no-repeat; \r\n	}\r\n\r\n#primary-nav li:hover, #primary-nav li.over { \r\n	background-color: #ABB0B6; \r\n	background-position: top right; \r\n	background-repeat: no-repeat; \r\n	}\r\n#primary-nav li li:hover, #primary-nav li li.over { \r\n	background-color: #ABB0B6; \r\n	background-image: none; \r\n	background-position: center right; \r\n	background-repeat: no-repeat; \r\n	}\r\n#primary-nav li.menuparent:hover, #primary-nav li.menuparent.over { \r\n	background-color: #ABB0B6; \r\n	background-position: center right; \r\n	background-repeat: no-repeat; \r\n	}\r\n#primary-nav li li.menuparent:hover, #primary-nav li li.menuparent.over { \r\n	background-image: url(modules/CSSMenu/images/arrow-right.gif); \r\n	background-position: center right; \r\n	background-repeat: no-repeat; \r\n	}\r\n#primary-nav li:hover ul ul, \r\n#primary-nav li:hover ul ul ul, \r\n#primary-nav li.over ul ul, \r\n#primary-nav li.over ul ul ul { \r\n	left: -999em; \r\n	}\r\n#primary-nav li:hover ul, \r\n#primary-nav li li:hover ul, \r\n#primary-nav li li li:hover ul, \r\n#primary-nav li.over ul, \r\n#primary-nav li li.over ul, \r\n#primary-nav li li li.over ul { \r\n	left: auto; \r\n	}	', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
INSERT INTO {DB_PREFIX}css ( CSS_ID, CSS_NAME, CSS_TEXT, MEDIA_TYPE, CREATE_DATE, MODIFIED_DATE ) VALUES ( 26, 'Default CSSMenu Vert', '#primary-nav, #primary-nav ul {\r\n  margin: 0;\r\n  padding: 0;\r\n  border-top: 1px solid #006699;\r\n  border-right: 1px solid #006699;\r\n  width: 100%; /* Width of Menu Items */\r\n  background: #ececec; /* IE6 Bug */\r\n  }\r\n\r\n#primary-nav ul {\r\n  border-left: 1px solid #006699;\r\n  }\r\n#primary-nav li {\r\n  position: relative;\r\n  list-style: none;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n#primary-nav li a {\r\n  display: block;\r\n  text-decoration: none;\r\n  padding: 5px 5px 5px 10px;\r\n  border-bottom: 1px solid #006699;\r\n  color: #18507C;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n/* Fix IE. Hide from IE Mac \\*/\r\n* html #primary-nav li { float: left; height: 1%; }\r\n* html #primary-nav li a { height: 1%; }\r\n/* End */\r\n\r\n#primary-nav ul {\r\n  position: absolute;\r\n  display: none;\r\n  left: 100%; /* Set 1px less than menu width */\r\n  top: -1px;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n#primary-nav li ul li a { padding: 5px 5px; } /* Sub Menu Styles */\r\n\r\n#primary-nav li:hover ul ul,\r\n#primary-nav li:hover ul ul ul,\r\n#primary-nav li.over ul ul,\r\n#primary-nav li.over ul ul ul { display: none; } /* Hide sub-menus initially */\r\n\r\n#primary-nav li:hover ul,\r\n#primary-nav li li:hover ul,\r\n#primary-nav li li li:hover ul,\r\n#primary-nav li.over ul,\r\n#primary-nav li li.over ul,\r\n#primary-nav li li li.over ul { display: block; } /* The magic */\r\n\r\n.cssmenu-vertical ul, #primary-nav li.menuparent { \r\n   background: #ececec url(modules/CSSMenu/images/arrow.gif) no-repeat right center; }\r\n\r\n/* fixed image flicker by adding .cssmenu-vertical ul */\r\n\r\n#primary-nav li.menuparent:hover, #primary-nav li.over { \r\n    background-color: #abb0b6;  \r\n   background: #ececec url(modules/CSSMenu/images/arrow.gif) no-repeat right center;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#primary-nav li a:hover {\r\n	background-color: #abb0b6;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#primary-nav .sectionheader { font-weight: bold;  background: #006699;  color: White; }\r\n\r\n.currentpage\r\n{\r\n	list-style-type: square;\r\n	display: inline;\r\n	background-color: #abb0b6;\r\n        color: #fff;\r\n}\r\n', '', '2005-11-29 09:26:29', '2005-11-29 09:26:29' );
